Term Deposit Sale¶

Goal¶

Using the data collected from existing customers, build a model that will help the marketing team identify potential customers who are relatively more likely to subscribe term deposit and thus increase their hit ratio.

def print_count(col, ordered=True):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15,8))
    plt.title(col)
    if ordered:
        ax = sns.countplot(raw_data[col], palette=palette, order=raw_data[col].value_counts().index)
    else:
        ax = sns.countplot(raw_data[col], palette=palette)
    
    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate('{:.0f}'.format(p.get_height()), (p.get_x()+.15, p.get_height()+1))

def print_kde(col):
    plt.figure(figsize=(25,5))
    sns.distplot(raw_data[col]);

def missing_check(df):
    total = df.isnull().sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
    percent = (df.isnull().sum()/df.isnull().count()).sort_values(ascending=False)
    md = pd.concat([total, percent], axis=1, keys=['Total', 'Percent'])
    
    return md

In [54]:
def plot_corr(df, size=11):
    corr = df.corr()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(size, size))
    ax.matshow(corr)
    plt.xticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
    plt.yticks(range(len(corr.columns)), corr.columns)
    for (i, j), z in np.ndenumerate(corr):
        ax.text(j, i, '{:0.1f}'.format(z), ha='center', va='center')

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
In [64]:
def calc_precision(tp, fp):
    return tp/(tp+fp)

def calc_recall(tp, fn):
    return tp/(tp+fn)

def calc_f1(tp, fp, fn):
    p = calc_precision(tp, fp)
    r = calc_recall(tp, fn)
    return 2*((p*r)/(p+r))

Model Analysis¶

Our objective here is to identify customers who are more likely to subscribe to term deposits. As the relative cost of a false positive - identifying a prospect who ultimately does not subscribe - is low, and has no negative impact on the business, we want to maximize identification of possible customers.

Because of this, maximizing recall is our primary objective, and we should use our 7-step capped Decision Tree. Should business context change, as the negative impact of false positives increases we would want to shift to a model more sensitive to precision, such as bagging or gradient boost.
